HEADWORD: Criminality
<hw>Crim`i*nal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(kr?m`?-n?l"?-t?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[LL. <ets>criminalitas</ets>, fr. L. <ets>criminalis</ets>. See
<er>Criminal</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being criminal;
that which constitutes a crime; guiltiness; guilt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is by no means the only criterion of
<qex>criminality</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>criminalize</ent>⟦br⟧
